            " into a ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "queen's pawn",
                "value": "the_centre_pawns"
            },
            " game."
        ]
    },
    "e4": {
        "description": [
            "White begins with a ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "King's Pawn Opening",
                "value": "the_centre_pawns",
                "punctuation": [null, ","]
            },
            " grabbing ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "space",
                "value": "space"
            },
            " and making a play for ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "control",
                "value": "control"
            },
            " of the ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "centre",
                "value": "centre",
                "punctuation": [null, "."]
            },
            "\nPushing the king's pawn also ",
            {
                "type": "glossary_button",
                "text": "opens up",
                "value": "piece_vision"
            },
            " the kingside bishop, facilitating the option of rapid kingside castling."
        ],
        "e5": {
            "description": [
                "Black mirrors, choosing the least confrontational way to contest White for the centre and take space",
                " for themselves in response."
            ],
            "Nf3": {
                "description": [
                    "White ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "develops",
                        "value": "development"
                    },
                    " a knight out towards the centre, exerting more influence there and simultaneously",
                    " threatening the e5 pawn.",
                    "\nDeveloping the kingside knight rather than the queenside knight maintains White's lead in",
                    " progress towards castling, which ",
                    {
                        "type": "wrap_italic",
                        "text": "can"
                    },
                    " build into an ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "advantage",
                        "value": "king_safety"
                    },
                    " if Black falls too far behind."
                ],
                "Nc6": {
                    "description": [
                        "Black develops a knight of their own to also further cover the centre, choosing the stable option",
                        " of the queenside knight as this adds a defender to the e5 pawn."
                    ],
                    "Bc4": {
                        "title": "Italian Game",
                        "description": [
                            "White develops their light-squared bishop, choosing a spot which has great presence in the",
                            " centre while being difficult to immediately harass, and adds pressure to the ",
                            {
                                "type": "glossary_button",
                                "text": "weak f7 square",
                                "value": "the_f_pawn",
                                "punctuation": [null, "."]
                            },
                            "\n\nBy developing both kingside minor pieces first, White is now ready to castle."
                        ],
                        "h6": {
                            "title": "Italian Game: Anti-Fried Liver Defence",
                            "annotation": "?!",
                            "board_arrows": [
                                ["f3", "g5"]
                            ],
                            "board_highlights": {
                                "g5": "var(--board-highlights-bad-color)"
                            },
                            "description": [
                                "Black ",
                                {
                                    "type": "glossary_button",
                                    "text": "denies",
                                    "value": "prophylaxis"
                                },
                                " the g5 square to White by covering it with the h-pawn. This prevents ",
                                {
                                    "type": "wrap_bold",
                                    "text": "Ng5"
                                },
                                " as would be played in certain lines such as this ",
                                {
                                    "type": "set_moves_button",
                                    "text": "alternative",
                                    "value": ["e4", "e5", "Nf3", "Nc6", "Bc4", "Nf6", "Ng5"],
                                    "punctuation": [null, ","]
                                },
                                " the aim of which is to add pressure to the f7 square generating a serious threat.",
                                "\n\nAlthough it prevents a clear plan of White's, this move unnecessarily delays both",
                                " development and progress towards castling - falling far enough behind that White now",
                                " has solid initiative to cause trouble for Black before they are ready to handle it",
                                " comfortably.",
                                "\nThere are other options available to handle the possibility of Ng5 which do not delay",
                                " development nor castling (for example ",
                                {
                                    "type": "set_moves_button",
                                    "text": "this",
                                    "value": "e4 e5 Nf3 Nc6 Bc4 Bc5 d3 Nf6 Ng5 O-O"
                                },
                                " line) and as such this move is ",
                                {
                                    "type": "eval_swing",
                                    "text": "inaccurate",
                                    "value": 0.5
                                },
                                " at the engine level.",
                                "\n\nWhite can best punish by ",
                                {
                                    "type": "glossary_button",
                                    "text": "cracking open",
                                    "value": "pawn_breaks"
                                },
                                " the centre to expose the kings with ",
                                {
                                    "type": "add_moves_button",
                                    "text": "d4",
                                    "value": "d4",
                                    "punctuation": [null, ","]
                                },
                                " playing on Black's inability to castle due to the undeveloped kingside knight and bishop",
                                " while White enjoys the privilege of being able to castle their own king to safety at a",
                                " moment's notice.",
                                "\nAlternatively, castling first and then playing d4 on the ",
                                {
                                    "type": "add_moves_button",
                                    "text": "next move",
                                    "value": "O-O Nf6 d4"
                                },
                                " is also a very strong option."
                            ]
                        }
                    }
                },
                "Nf6": {
                    "title": "Petrov's Defence",
                    "board_arrows": [["f3", "e5"], ["f6", "e4"]],
                    "description": [
                        "Instead of defending their own pawn, Black ",
                        {
                            "type": "glossary_button",
                            "text": "counters",
                            "value": "counterattacks"
                        },
                        " by threatening White's pawn."
                    ],
                    "Nxe5": {
                        "Nxe4": {
                            "title": "Petrov's Defence: Damiano Variation",
