        "d5": {
            "description": [
                "Black mirrors, choosing the least confrontational way to contest White for the centre and take space",
                " for themselves in response."
            ],
            "c4": {
                "title": "Queen's Gambit",
                "description": [
                    "White immediately challenges Black's pawn on d5. This ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "gambit",
                        "value": "gambits"
                    },
                    " offers up ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "the c-pawn",
                        "value": "using_the_c_pawn",
                        "punctuation": [null, ","]
                    },
                    " tempting Black to give up central control by capturing it.",
                    "\n\nAccepting the gambit ",
                    {
                        "type": "wrap_italic",
                        "text": "very"
                    },
                    " slightly ",
                    {
                        "type": "eval_swing",
                        "text": "favours",
                        "value": 0.1
                    },
                    " White, although the swing is insignificant in practical terms. If Black accepts, White is given",
                    " initiative to seize control of the centre for themselves, and will find it fairly easy to scoop up",
                    " Black's ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "now-overextended",
                        "value": "overextension"
                    },
                    " pawn on c4 down the line even if Black dedicates resources to defending it.",
                    "\nThe reason that accepting the gambit does not afford White a ",
                    {
                        "type": "wrap_italic",
                        "text": "bigger"
                    },
                    " advantage, despite this benefit, is simply that Black still has options available to them in the",
                    " resulting position with which they can effectively contest White's claim on the centre."
                ],
                "e6": {
                    "title": "Queen's Gambit Declined",
                    "description": [
                        "Rather than capturing, Black reinforces their d-pawn with the e-pawn, attempting to",
                        " cement their place in the centre.",
                        "\nThis move also ",
                        {
                            "type": "glossary_button",
                            "text": "opens up",
                            "value": "piece_vision"
                        },
                        " the kingside bishop, giving Black a slight lead in progress towards kingside castling, but",
                        " simultaneously encloses the queenside bishop inside the newly created ",
                        {
                            "type": "glossary_button",
                            "text": "pawn chain",
                            "value": "pawn_structures"
                        },
                        " hampering Black's ability to impactfully ",
                        {
                            "type": "glossary_button",
                            "text": "develop",
                            "value": "development"
                        },
                        " it."
                    ],
                    "Nc3": {
                        "description": [
                            "White develops their first minor piece, bringing the queen's knight out under the c-pawn",
                            " to the position where it has the best coverage of the centre.",
                            "\nThis also adds pressure to the d5 pawn, limiting Black's options for development in the",
                            " short term by preventing any moves that would obstruct the queen's defence of it."
                        ],
                        "Nf6": {
                            "description": [
                                "Black develops their kingside knight and ",
                                {
                                    "type": "glossary_button",
                                    "text": "overprotects",
                                    "value": "overprotection"
                                },
                                " the d5 pawn. This avoids blocking in the c-pawn, which the only sensible option for",
                                " developing the queenside knight instead in this position (",
                                {
                                    "type": "wrap_bold",
                                    "text": "Nc6"
                                },
                                ") would do."
                            ]
                        },
                        "Nd7": {
                            "annotation": "?",
                            "board_arrows": [
                                ["d8", "d5"]
                            ],
                            "board_highlights": {
                                "d7": "var(--board-highlights-bad-color)"
                            },
                            "description": [
                                "Black develops their queenside knight towards the centre, placing it on d7 which avoids",
                                " blocking in their c-pawn with it.",
                                "\n\nUnfortunately, this move instead blocks the vision of Black's queen over their d5",
                                " pawn, leaving it insufficiently defended and open to capture with no real ",
                                {
                                    "type": "glossary_button",
                                    "text": "compensation",
                                    "value": "imbalances"
                                },
                                " for its sacrifice. ",
                                {
                                    "type": "eval_swing",
                                    "value": 0.9
                                }
                            ],
                            "cxd5": {
                                "annotation": "!",
                                "description": [
                                    "White takes the under-defended d5 pawn, and after the ",
                                    {
                                        "type": "add_moves_button",
                                        "text": "exchange",
                                        "value": ["exd5", "Nxd5"]
                                    },
                                    " concludes will simply be up material."
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
